===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|seyen}}, {{m|enm|seien}}, {{m|enm|seggen}}, from {{inh|en|ang|seċġan||to say, speak}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*sagjaną||to say}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*sokʷ-h₁-yé-}}, a suffixed ''o''-grade form of {{m|ine-pro|*sekʷ-||to tell, talk|id=say}}. Cognate with {{cog|fy|sizze||to say}}, {{cog|nl|zeggen||to say}}, {{cog|de|sagen||to say}}, {{cog|da|sige||to say}}, {{cog|nb|si||to say}}, {{cog|nn|seia||to say}}, {{cog|sv|säga||to say}}.

The adverb and interjection are from the verb.
